cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DC 

The paper discusses the application of network coding in multimedia systems, which involves aspects of networking (cs.NI), multimedia (cs.MM), information theory (cs.IT), system and control (cs.SI), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). However, since the paper focuses on the practical implementation of network coding in multimedia systems, cs.NI and cs.MM are the most likely categories.
